Phil Karn (karn@unix.ka9q.ampr.org) wrote:

: I held up one of our new CD-7000 dual-mode FM/CDMA cellular phones and
: pointed to the connector on the bottom. Through it you can, if you
: figure out how, reburn the flash EPROM inside the phone with any
: software you like, including encryption software. (Caveat: flash
: EPROMs are still relatively expensive, and production versions of the
: phone may go to mask ROM, which is much cheaper.)

Is it possible that Qualcomm could "make public" the specs, for
kit-builders to make these mods? If Ciarcia was still doing his
"Circuit Cellar" series for "Byte," this would be a natural.

(I wonder if some arcane law says it "illegal" for Phil or for
Qualcomm to even _talk_ about how to do it?)

-Tim May

